cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

The paper deals with the task of RGBT tracking, which involves computer vision and machine learning techniques for object tracking using both visible spectrum and thermal infrared data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel deep learning framework for RGBT tracking, which involves feature learning and adaptation, making it relevant to categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves experiments on benchmark datasets, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper also mentions the need for real-time tracking, which is relevant to the category of cs.RO (Robotics).
